<div class="ingredients">
    <h3><strong>Ingredients</strong></h3>
    <ul>
        <li>2 cups all purpose flour</li>
        <li>3/4 cups sugar</li>
        <li>3 1/2 teaspoons baking powder</li>
        <li>2 large eggs</li>
        <li>1 1/2 cups milk</li>
        <li>2 sticks (1 cup) butter, melted</li>
        <li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
        <li>toppings of your choice</li>
    </ul>

    <h3><strong>Directions</strong></h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Beat the eggs, sugar, vanilla, and melted butter (make sure it is not too hot or it will scramble the eggs) in a large bowl.</li>
        <li>Add the flour, baking powder and half of the milk. Mix well.</li>
        <li>Slowly add the remaining milk will mixing. If the batter is obviously too thick, add more milk.</li>
        <li>Turn on your waffle iron and let the batter rest for 10-30 minutes.</li>
        <li>Pour about 3/4 cup of batter into your iron, or whatever your iron is designed for. Cook until the steam escaping your iron is almost gone, or according to your waffle iron's instructions.</li>
        <li>To keep the cooked waffles crispy while you cook the rest of the batter, store them on a rack in the oven. We do not recommend stacking the waffles as that will cause steam from the lower ones to absorb into the ones above it.</li>
    </ol>
